  "text": "Palla and his colleagues presented CPM to discover an overlapping community structure [CITATION_1] . They assumed that a network community is made of \"adjacent\" k cliques, which share at least k − 1 nodes with each other. Each clique uniquely belongs to one community, but cliques within different communities may share nodes. Using the above heuristic information, CPM is able to find the overlaps of communities. For a given K, CPM first locates all k cliques (k ≤ K ) from a given network, and then build a clique-clique overlap matrix to find out communities in terms of different k. But in practice, for an unknown network, it is not easy to decide what value of k will result in a more reasonable community structure.",
